  "texts": [
    "The dataset contains 5,000 finely annotated images and 20,000 roughly annotated images.",
    "The dataset has been widely used as a benchmark for developing algorithms for semantic segmentation [74] and instance segmentation [75], providing two significant challenges for these fields.BDD100K: Berkeley Deep Drive 100K (BDD100K) is a diverse and large-scale visual driving scene dataset that was proposed, collected, and annotated by [76].",
    "It introduces a new benchmark for visual driving tasks.",
    "In most use cases, the images in BDD100K are annotated with three basic types of labels: image-level tags, bounding boxes, and polygon annotations.",
    "However, the semantic interpretation of these annotations can vary significantly across different use cases."
